The paper proposes a novel method for unsupervised image-to-image translation, which involves attention modules and learnable normalization functions. This work is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) tasks, specifically image-to-image translation, which suggests that cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the use of attention modules and learnable normalization functions indicates that the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), graphics (cs.GR), and multimedia (cs.MM).
